.LC.LCAN07.SCH1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="schedule" searchtype="LEGISLATION SCHEDULE" subdoc="false" toc-caption="[LCA07 Sch 1] SCHEDULE 1 PROVISIONS RELATING TO MAGISTRATES"><leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.PT4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="part" searchtype="LEGISLATION PART" subdoc="false" toc-caption="PART 4 ACTING MAGISTRATES">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="PART-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.PT4" type="ext"/>PART 4</designum></desig><title searchtype="PART-TITLE">ACTING MAGISTRATES</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="clause" searchtype="LEGISLATION CLAUSE" subdoc="true" toc-caption="cl 12 Acting Magistrates">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><title searchtype="CLAUSE-TITLE"><refpt id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12" type="ext"/>Acting Magistrates</title><desig searchtype="CLAUSE-NUM"><designum>12</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subclause" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBCLAUSE">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An acting Magistrate has the powers and authorities of a Magistrate, is to fulfil the duties of a Magistrate and for the purposes of this or any other Act (other than the 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="OTH.STAT" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Statutory and Other Offices Remuneration Act 1975</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
) is taken to be a Magistrate.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subclause" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBCLAUSE">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A person appointed as an acting Magistrate may, despite the expiration of the person&#x2019;s term of office, complete or otherwise continue to hear and determine and otherwise deal with any proceedings that have been heard, or partly heard, by the person before the expiration of that term.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subclause" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBCLAUSE">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>While a person continues to deal with or determine, under 
<ci:cite searchtype="LEG-REF"><ci:content><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.2" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">subclauseÂ (2)</remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>
, any proceedings that have been heard or partly heard by the person before the expiration of the person&#x2019;s term of office, the person has all the entitlements and functions of a Magistrate and, for the purposes of those proceedings, is taken to continue to be a Magistrate.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subclause" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBCLAUSE">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.LC.LCAN07.SCH1.CL12.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A person appointed as an acting Magistrate is entitled to be paid such remuneration as the Governor considers appropriate and such travelling and subsistence allowances as the Minister may from time to time determine in respect of the Magistrate.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
